{"product_id": "275080", "page": 1, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "23 November, 2021", "text": "Interesting premise, terrible execution. Very little to salvage.\nThe graphics are bad, but in a management game that will easily get a free pass. Transport Tycoon had worse graphics (not much, maybe slightly worse, but worse), and it still is one of my favorite games ever, so let's put that down as an \"average\" mark, 5/10.\nSound is frankly appalling. A short loop as music, cringeworthy sound effect on random actions. Some of them I feel are ripped straight from some 1970s German porn movie. 1/10, and I am being generous\nThe strategy approach at first sparks a glimpse of interest: managing the routes and tasks of every vehicle in the fleet, connecting different post offices... maybe we have something good here? in short, NO.\nThere are 6 vehicle tasks, one of them basically useless. The type of vehicle limits the range and load available for the job, but the steep difference in price and the unlock cost make it a slow unbearable agony getting anything other than a motobike or basic car.\nManagement of the post office is basic to the point of being insulting. The upgrades have practically no effect and -once you buy all 9 employees- office management is over.\nStarting funds are limited (rightfully so), but even by wisely spending them all, building either one large office or two interconnected medium ones, or three small ones, money trickle in so slowly that playing the game is a pointless waiting task. It could be an idle game, save for the fact that sometimes you have to click to proceed to the next day.\nOne week into the game you may have been able to buy an extra car or two, or better yet repair stations for all your offices. The next step would be a new office but -I assure you- you will drop the game well before this happens.\nYou may be gaining 3000 a day, and it takes 35k+ to set up a new office. Playing for 10 in-game days, even if played at fastest speed, is as fun as having your hand crushed into a meat grinder.\nLet's say the gameplay is a 2/10 overall, a score bumped up only by the lack of alternative in postal managament games.\nThis game shows a utter and complete lack of balancing, playtesting or refinement. It is extremely clear it has been abandoned mid-development and rushed to finish it to a quasi-working condition.\nThe only players who can possibly enjoy this are comatose patients with an OCD and a lifelong passion for post offices, but I feel it is a very small -even if totally untapped- market niche.\nPlease do yourself a solid, avoid this dumpst... postbox fire, and spend your 5‚Ç¨ in something more fast-paced such as a stamps collection or a pet rock.", "hours": 1.3, "user_id": "76561197980248095", "username": "cantoni.federico", "products": 376, "early_access": false}
