{"product_id": "344340", "page": 1, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "24 July, 2021", "text": "I have to say that this game will never stand up to Head Coach 08. The game simulation is lame and this is all about fast pace get through the year to get to draft.  I need the full experience of running a team, the screens leave a lot to be desired and you don't get a true picture of the players. I would rate this game as a 4 out of 10!", "hours": 42.3, "user_id": "76561199123310334", "username": "Buckethead", "products": 15, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "344340", "page": 1, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "13 June, 2021", "text": "I bought the game a few years ago and decided to go back to it.  It did not take long for me to learn why I stopped playing.  I play against the AI and I have found the Free Agent process is broken.  I have gone to the extreme level of offering players 5X the amount other teams have offered and they still choose to go with the lower offer.  This is for players that supposedly have low loyalty.  The choice was not made due to the composition of the compensation, I have multiplied each years salary and the bonus by 5 and still they would not move.  Trades are also extremely lopsided.  Other teams only offer dumb trades and they wont accept your offers even if they slightly favor the other team.  The game touts and even has its name based on the Front Office but two very important pieces are very broken.", "hours": 256.1, "user_id": "76561198006735451", "username": "gkmetty", "products": 304, "early_access": false}
