{"product_id": "230820", "page": 1, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "28 December, 2021", "text": "This game is quite a fun little adventure if you like the point and click style, it was not too trying.\nThe story very much has to do with coming of age in a world that is stiffling out the natural wonder of our world into something more artificial. The ending, was a bit disappointing through as I think it lost focus of the narrative and it was kind of anti-climaxtic. The journey is good through.\nThe delightful characters saved this one as it is a middling positive.", "hours": 16.2, "username": "Tantroo", "products": 302, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "27900", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "13 January", "text": "5/10 for originality, 4/10 for functionality, yet it has its charm.\n\nThis game is clearly heavily inspired by Portal, but the game lacks refinement to be a good game. Positioning objects and yourself is pure jank. Obviously I wasn't willing to continue past an hour playtime, yet I have too soft a spot for this game to disrecommend it. First of all, this from 2009! It doesn't look all that bad for its age! It's certainly no asset flip (did those exist back then?) and that alone is a big plus by today's standard. It's sci-fi, that's also a plus with me.\nYeah it's super jank, but it doesn't crash at least.\nNo I don't recommend buying this. But if you happen to own this and you feel adventurous, I'd say give it a go! It isn't complete trash.", "hours": 0.8, "username": "TNTFTB", "products": 2180, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "27900", "page": 1, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "6 December, 2021", "text": "Anyone comparing this to Portal needs to have their head examined.\nThe player movement is quite stiff and the mouse movement is pretty laggy.\nThe story seems alright, but due to the above mentioned issue, I probably wont finish it.\nThere are no audio settings beyond language and subtitles (on/off) and the video settings are very basic; limited to resolution, windowed/fullscreen, vsync, gamma, shadows (on/off), glow (on/off) and soft particles (on/off).", "hours": 1.3, "username": "pHJ", "products": 680, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "27900", "page": 1, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "23 November, 2021", "text": "Cool mechanic idea and terrible execution. Random modern PCs seem to have a glitch where the camera bobs up and down all the time with no way to fix. The game has somewhat OK puzzles up until the turrets show up, and then the entire game becomes dodge the bullets and loading screens from the numerous deaths that you will go through. The puzzles seem half baked and don't seem to incorporate the game mechanics or physics properly. The fall damage seems way too intense for a game that requires you to fall down half the time. Didn't finish the game after the 10th level out of 17, and you shouldn't even start it. If you're even curious about it, the story doesn't really have much to offer for the small bits you even get, and it's as predictable as it seems. Just play Portal or a different game instead. Thanks for reading and have a good day! :)", "hours": 3.7, "username": "Downtown Coolsville", "products": 107, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "27900", "page": 1, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "9 October, 2021", "text": "Incredibly weird atmosphere. I'm only recommending that because they have managed to create something beautifully unique in that. However, the level design is abysmal. In fact, I think the developers only put this game in the puzzle genre because its confuses the ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• out of any normal human plays it. The story is also quite interesting... Honestly to sum this up, if you enjoy a good plot enough to subject yourself to this game, then I wish you luck.", "hours": 6.7, "user_id": "76561198066235025", "username": "Jack", "products": 231, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "27900", "page": 1, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "1 July, 2021", "text": "So, i wouldn't call this a good game, but also not a bad game.\nThe puzzles aren't too complicated and only really the turrets are a big ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• you to the player, but only sometimes.\nyou might die a lot at portions, but who wants a game where you can just breeze through.\nPeople compare it to portal, but apart from both being about solving puzzles and surviving, i would't really compare them.\nI'm pretty sure they too inspiration from portal though (if you get this game, you know why)\nI enjoyed it, despite the frustrating moments and the ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• movement scheme (no sprinting and forward is the only fast way to move)\nSome tips though:\nyour gloves don't reach into infinity. if you're aiming at something too far away it won't work (notice the cross hair)\nWhen a terminal doesn't tell you it's not working, you might have to hold the activation button. The game doesn't tell you about this.\nDon't be afraid to think outside the box. Some portions can be solved without doing it the intended way, luckily it's usually the ones you want to skip too.", "hours": 8.9, "user_id": "76561198065345209", "username": "R5N250E24", "products": 127, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "27900", "page": 1, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "25 May, 2021", "text": "It feels a little like portal but with push & pull one click pulls the other pushes. You can tell it's from a small dev, as it loads excruciatingly slow. The Menus are fairly bad taking you to the main menu where while playing a game you don't expect to see \"new game\" or \"load game\" but you expect \"resume\". I think the idea is fine, the execution is lacking.", "hours": 0.7, "username": "fangerzero", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
