{"product_id": "260930", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "15 January", "text": "Not optimized for modern systems.\nI got a physical copy of Emergency 2012 Deluxe as a gift in 2012 and I ran it on a toaster without any issues. No stuttering, no crashing, nothing. Not a single issue playing for 3 years. Now I wanted to relive the nostalgia a bit because I think Quadriga's games are a wee bit misunderstood but apparently I forgot game devs don't care much about their product once it's on the shelves.\nIntel i5-8000-something, 16 GB DDR 4 RAM, Nvidia GTX 1050 Ti. So it should run better than back then, right?\nHahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahahaha\nStuttering, looooots of stuttering. I was only able to get into freeplay. As soon as you move the camera, slideshow. What about the missions? Crashes straight after the cinematic every time and even freeplay crashed on me for seemingly no reason at all. Stay away from this one. If even Emergency 20 runs like hot crap on capable systems you bet this one's worse.", "hours": 0.5, "username": "Delinquent", "products": 127, "early_access": false}
