{"product_id": "275080", "page": 2, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2020-05-31", "text": "This actually had the makings of a decent strategy/sim-lite game, but somewhere along the way the developers of Post Master decided it'd be far more fun if the game played itself. Never mind you paid for it, you don't really need to play it outside of the tutorial and maybe another 15 minutes to set up your postal empire. Check back every ten minutes to fetch a priority delivery if you wish...or not, it doesn't much matter. There are robbers, but they never appear once you hire security for each post office. You have several vehicles to choose from once you...*ahem* the game...earns enough bonus stars, but you can play through PM just fine with the starting bicycles if you wish. All of the post offices look the same as your starting one except they have slightly fewer staff slots. The game world has decent building models but the soundtrack is glaringly irritating after a few minutes.\nIdle and clicker style games are all the rage these days, but Post Master goes too far with the whole idling thing. There is nothing here, it's just a time waster that doesn't even have a few easy achievements to unlock. Barring a major overhaul, I can't ever see myself touching this title again. Neither should you.", "hours": 1.6, "username": "Hairy Goober", "products": 3917, "early_access": false}
