{"product_id": "275080", "page": 2, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2019-11-03", "text": "Post Master is a business simulator where you control a post office company and send letters and parcels around the place.  Build offices and postboxes, buy a fleet of delivery vans.\nThere's two kinds of terrible games on Steam, the most common kind is where a reasonable game idea is implemented badly, and the less common, where a terrible idea is implemented at all.   This concept here is incredibly dry... at least with Sim City and similar games you get to see your city grow as you make business decisions to run the local economy.   Here, you don't even get that.   The implementation isn't terrible, but I just found myself asking why???\nJust play Sim City.   You can get that for cheaper than this with the whopping $7.50 price tag for a game that has less going for it than Sim City 2000.", "hours": 1.1, "user_id": "76561198030784015", "username": "Obey the Fist!", "products": 6169, "early_access": false}
