{"product_id": "314020", "page": 2, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2021-06-23", "text": "I would have liked to give this a good review, it had a highly imaginative premise insects and whatnot, but where it fell down was the menus and puzzles.\nFrom the start you get plonked down into the undergrowth and it is with sheer luck you find out what to do to move things along. I am no stranger to this type of game but a game of this size that has so many online tutorials and walkthroughs tells you that something is amiss. I mean I am not suggesting they you the way to do it but a little better hint engine would move things along in the right direction. What happens when you cannot figure out where to go or what to do and decide to come back to the puzzle later, nothing that what. You have to force close the game and then restart the chapter.\nAnd now to the final matter. All the puzzles in this game were of an  easy to moderate level, solvable with just a few moves, all except for the last one which is like a Rubik's cube on speed. If there was a graduated puzzle difficulty building up to the last one I could understand but the last one is so vastly different and difficult I lost interest and gave up after the first 25 moves.", "hours": 5.5, "username": "byrnensorg", "products": 29, "early_access": false}
