{"product_id": "314020", "page": 2, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2021-04-13", "text": "this is a wonderful hidden object/puzzle game to just chill and relax with. the art is absolutely beautiful, and the gameplay is fairly simple.\nthe only issue i have is that sometimes it's a little difficult to find one of the objects you're supposed to be clicking on, because it can blend into the environment a little too well. however, there is a hint button that will point it out to you as long as it's on the same screen. the puzzles you encounter in each level don't come with instructions either, but with the exception of one or two of them i was able to catch onto what i was supposed to do pretty quickly.\ni would really love to see another game in this style with a different setting.", "hours": 3.3, "username": "CrashBandiQT", "products": 300, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "314020", "page": 2, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2021-04-10", "text": "A hidden object style game with lovely art but largely spoiled by bad controls. The hidden objects are either too easy or quite obscured. The movement of your bug is too slow and finicky with the pathing getting confused and often mleaves you moving between screens when you really don`t want to which only adds to the frustration. The sequence you need to collect the items often requires backtracking having to endure the slow and awkward movement. The music tries to provide some calm but by this point it`s a lost cause, HOG rage has set in.\nThe art is really good, it`s a shame the game can`t back it up with better gameplay.", "hours": 6.5, "user_id": "76561198180063266", "username": "d00fington", "products": 7494, "early_access": false}
