{"product_id": "27900", "page": 2, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2020-01-27", "text": "This is legitimately the worst game I have in my library. It's over bloated, excessively rehashed, and a terrible knock-off of the seminal puzzle game Portal. Even the fact that Twin Sector is A$3 and Portal is around A$15 should not be an excuse to purchase this game.\nI purchased this game when i was young and had no money. I have since regretted the sub A$5 i spent on this game and the 6+ hours i spent literally slogging through this game, the last hour of which i resorted to using god mode. Not because it was too difficult, but because the \"puzzles\" were excessively asinine and completely over used.\nTL;DR - Do Not Buy This Game.", "hours": 7.1, "user_id": "76561198018713519", "username": "BigmanAU", "products": 186, "early_access": false}
