{"product_id": "275080", "page": 3, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2018-03-19", "text": "Post Master is kind of like a mobile game made for PC. It has clumsy menus, no hotkeys, represents information poorly, offers little actual control over what you do and requires you to do menial tasks (hire/buy X of Y) to unlock cars and office upgrades.\nAll post offices look the same, cars have been lazily named (e.g. \"superior truck\") and the 'city' is a bizarre patchwork of semi-randomly placed blocks that looks nothing like an actual city.\nDays pass by extremely slowly even at the highest speed and there's a prompt at the start of each day which pauses the game and you can't disable it.\nIt claims to be a sim but it's more a casual clicking game without any depth or things to accomplish.", "hours": 3.5, "username": "anarchistica", "products": 1154, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "275080", "page": 3, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-03-14", "text": "For the 1st few minutes I was indeed in the WTF do I do moments...lol However, if you have an IQ over 12 or have gamed for more than a year and have gaming taste beyond a 5 game or one genre capacity....it's not difficult to figure out or enjoy. As for the game itself, this is a very casual game, there is some pretty nice strategy moments in trying to figure out how to place your boxes, offices and the right trucks to cover the most distance which = the most profit. On higher levels it can be quite challenging with a competent AI that will not \"play\" with you but will wipe the floor with you instead. It's made for casual yet meaningful fun for those who enjoy taking a break from Call Of Duty..lol I like the graphics, nice 2d isometric city layouts and buidlings and since my tastes are far and wide from intense hardcore strategy, to COD and BAttlefield FPS, to micromangament hell 4x brain busters. I find this game , as with Zoo World (one of their other little casuals) very relaxing, allowing me to watch and play with my routes and offices, use enough brain poweer to stay awake, yet still remain in a relaxed but interested causal state. For 5$ it would be alright, for a buck on sale it's more for that buck than most of you cheap cheesers deserve..lmao\nRecommended for those with enough variety of taste to play a casual little strategy game.", "hours": 4.5, "username": "Redrusty66", "products": 1932, "early_access": false}
