{"product_id": "27900", "page": 3, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2018-08-22", "text": "Tags: Adventure - WS - Creative Walker\nAdditional Tags: Delete Local Content & Remove from Library\nTLDR: This is an attract/repel gloves physics based corridor leverpull cutscene walksim with dated engine, derivative setting and finnicky core mechanics.\nGame is a lot like Magnetic: Cage Closed. Older, but uses the same fundamental idea of grappling unto objects and throwing force on the floor tiles to jump. The game uses a vault dweller / system shock cryogenis awakening sci fi type setting. The levels are linear corridors with switches to open. The physics oriented gameplay means deaths and setbacks are plenty.\nConclusion: Platforming in physics oriented corridor walker can make or break a game, and while the mechanics in this case actually work as intended, they are not engaging at all. I would rather play a dedicated physics oriented puzzle game or a dedicated first person platformer separately. The activation and release of abilities is slow. The cutscenes are poorly voice acted. Texturing is poor all around. Altogether a very skippable title. Removing permanently for declutter.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "2nd Class Janitor - Wilco", "products": 3302, "early_access": false}
