{"product_id": "324610", "page": 1, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "31 October, 2018", "text": "This \"game\" is a waste of time.  You click on a gift (or sometimes your not even allowed that much control), then you click on an item in your mum-in-laws office, then you select a few levels of dialog to get one of 4 or 5 endings.  Sometimes those selections seem to make sense to the ending, sometimes they are nothing to do with it.\nFrankly this seems like someone had a decent idea for a branching storytelling framework, did the artwork for the shop, a few branches and then thought \"I can't be bothered to put any more effort into this\" but released it anyway.", "hours": 0.6, "username": "ieuan_johns", "products": 516, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "324610", "page": 1, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "6 August, 2018", "text": "I'm sorry, but this game feels like either there is no actual ending, or it was executed very poorly so that hardly anyone can figure out the exact sequence to progress or gain any further story.\nI can love games with rewinding features, as long as it actually reveals more depthy beneath it. This did not provide any depth whatsoever and was quite boring after 5 minutes.\nI will say though, the structure of the game is a foot in the right direction. I can appreciate the hand-drawn art and graphics, and the voiceovers. These are excellent qualities for any game, of any genre. I hope that the developer makes a better game next time and learn from their mistakes.", "hours": 0.6, "username": "Banshee", "products": 397, "early_access": false}
