{"product_id": "342450", "page": 1, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "11 July, 2020", "text": "While it has nicer art than most visual novels I've played, a visual novel is primarily about the story and this one has a lot less story than most of the games in the genre.  I've played FREE visual novels that told a better story.  The choices lead to different places, but several playthroughs show that it pretty much leads to your character falling in love with like... the one cute guy she met at the beginning.  Playthroughs are super short with not much in the way of plot.  It ends when the guy likes the girl enough.  In one playthrough, you talk to the guy about all these conflicts you got to resolve, he falls for you and it's The End.  And most of the time, there really isn't much of a reason for the two characters to fall in love?\nIf you liked those old choose your story books from the 80's, trust me that there are a lot more games like this with much more plot.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198136308258", "username": "dragonphoenix", "products": 45, "early_access": false}
