{"product_id": "314020", "page": 4, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2020-11-29", "text": "Short Version:\nPros:\n+ Charming presentation\n+ Relaxing gameplay\n+ Soothing soundtrack\nCons:\n- Very short\n- Controls can be clunky\n\"Long\" Version:\nis a point and click puzzle game.\nYou control several insects and must find items in order to proceed.\nThere is no real story to experience here.\nGameplay is very basic but enjoyable, nonetheless. Every interaction is click-based. You move your insect around from area to area and you collect a certain number of objects to move onto the next level. Movement can feel a bit janky at times, which leads to ‚Äúlengthy‚Äù area transitions when you accidentally move to another area. Movement around the edges is the only problematic part of the gameplay ‚Äì everything else works as it should.\nSome items might be a bit annoying to find.\nApart from moving around collecting items, you also have to solve a few puzzles but those are rather simple.\n‚Äô soundtrack is really enjoyable. It is very soothing and it fits the theme.\nThe art-style is gorgeous, every area is hand-drawn and it looks stunning. The color pallete usage is impeccable too.\nThe game is really short ‚Äì you can finish it in 2 hours or less. There is no replay value.\nis a neat, inexpensive game that is worth trying if you enjoy strong visual direction and nature.\nFinal score: 7 out of 10.\nIf you enjoyed this review, please consider joining my\nand following my\non Steam.", "hours": 1.7, "compensation": "Product received for free", "username": "Good Guy Nick", "products": 929, "early_access": false}
