{"product_id": "246960", "page": 4, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-10-09", "text": "No disrespect to those that have played and loved the lineage of the games, it is upon those recommendations that I made the purchase.\nHowever as a new initiate to this game, the characters, and the intended play style it is just too much for me and frankly, far too difficult to give me the enjoyment I want out of a platformer.\nI have always considered myself a good platformer, going right back to the NES days and even well before that on PC and I have played a wide range, so I don't feel my criticisms are all that out of line.\nMy real objection to this game is that it really requires absolute precision in every input throughout every level.  Memorization is absolutely essential and I found myself completely dazzled and unable to immediately asses each new situation until dying several times every screen.  The graphics are lovely but they do the player no favors in helping quickly figure out what is going on and where you are allowed to go.\nAfter about 30 minutes I realized that I don't want to play a memorization game and a completely unforgiving platformer where there are spikes and other hazards on pretty much every single surface.  I knew right from the get-go that I was in for a rough ride when the first level was a race against time and I died 30 times just acquainting myself with the controls.\nI can only go on my personal experience, and I would think that unless you have a history of enjoying the other games in the series take a pass, because it's hard AF and frankly not a forgiving game in any way which for me amounted to mostly frustration.", "hours": 3.2, "username": "KrudlerTheHorse", "products": 707, "found_funny": 5, "early_access": false}
