{"product_id": "344340", "page": 4, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-07", "text": "Since I was a young kid, one of my favorite things to do was put in a sports game and draft a team.  This experience was always fun, no matter what sport: baseball, football, basketball, hockey, if I could put together a team that would build off the strengths of the various players and experiment to turn that team into a finely-tuned machine, that was my after-school jam.\nThis game has been addicting to me.  Unfortunately, I haven't taken many teams past 3 years; my excitement over drafting and re-drafting doesn't allow me to continue through with balancing the team budget, working through the dangerous waters of free agency, or watching the guys I originally drafted leave for greener grasses elsewhere.  But if you're looking for a decent GM-simulator, this is the place to be.\nJust don't expect fancy graphics when you simulate the games.  It's not all the way down to a bare-bones text sim, but you're not paying for the graphics if you buy this game.  You're paying for a fairly robust franchise-building experience, but one without much eye candy.", "hours": 113.9, "username": "LeperSaint09", "products": 233, "early_access": false}
