{"product_id": "292180", "page": 4, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2019-12-31", "text": "It's a Flight Simulator, So that in of itself tells you a lot of what you need to know right off the boat.\nIt's flight model works differently from FSX (and presumably the new one Microsoft has made more recently), and because of that, it is possible to make your own aircraft completely from scratch, and the game will do it's level best to accurately simulate them. This will either be the most fun you can have in a flight sim, or incredibly frustrating, depending on your talent with aeronautics or inclination on making things. to be honest, this is 80% of what I do in this game.\nThere are scenery packs you can install to make things look a bit better, but without even playing 11, I can tell you it's a better choice then 10 unless your hardware is a bit older. The sounds are a mixed bag, some aircraft are great, some not so much. Combat in this game exists, but it so rudementery that it's not really worth messing with too much. However, there are carriers to land on, air tankers to refuel at, and AI fighters if you want to do that. For peaceful operations, you've got a bazillion little airports, and all of the VORs and ADFs you need to get there, as well as GPS. It's pretty easy to set up any number of joysticks or button boxes to control everything as well.", "hours": 71.6, "username": "DFX2KX", "products": 310, "early_access": false}
