{"product_id": "342450", "page": 2, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2020-06-29", "text": "Not an action or adventure game, more Choose Your Own Adventure, which causes the game to feel mis-advertised, as one other review seems to point out, and is probably what kills the game the most.\nThe \"Elven Romance\" is extremely rushed, with no development or character from either the main or the love interest. A few sentences are all it take to be deeply in love which isn't believable even in a Fantasy with orcs and a dragon\nThe paths tend to be very short, and nothing about this world or what is going is explained...which might work were this not represented as an Epic Fantasy where you might expect actual combat or action scenes. No personalities, no action, no humor, extremely little emotion (The death of Tyrna's father at the start)...it just completely lacks substance other than admittedly gorgeous artwork.\nA good story can save bad artwork, but good artwork can't save a bad story.\nIf a simple Choose Your Own Adventure is up your ally, wait until this one is on sale, I can't recommend this one otherwise.", "hours": 0.8, "user_id": "76561198381423002", "username": "Shadowwing09", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "342450", "page": 2, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2020-06-27", "text": "The story is short, and I do wish the characters were more developped, but for that low price it's really good! I think it's actually to its advantage, since there are so many endings! I don't think I would have the motivation to find out that many endings if it was longer. The story is still engaging and interesting. It comes from a choose-your-own-adventure book from the 80's after all!\nThe artwork is stunning. It reminds me fondly of my D&D sessions before the pandemic hit!", "hours": 1.9, "user_id": "76561198066223501", "username": "Mitzi", "products": 32, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "342450", "page": 2, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2020-04-25", "text": "Sword daughter was an entertaining choices-matter style interactive story. I loved the overall premise, the story twists, and the artwork. I particularly enjoyed that one of the features, accessible from the main menu, was a plot map that allowed you to see which paths hadn't yet been explored. I liked that it was easy to go back and forth between the various story lines to try to see the different outcomes, without having to resort to a guide/walkthrough in order to see everything.\nWhat could have made the game better?\nSeveral aspects of the game could have been better.\nOverall, Sword Daughter is a solid story from Hanako Games, and recommended to anyone who loves choice driven narratives with female protagonists.", "hours": 4.5, "username": "spiritedrinoa", "products": 558, "early_access": false}
