{"product_id": "324610", "page": 2, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-05-03", "text": "The french have a way of thinking about art, they say \"l'art pour l'art\" - it's just art for arts sake.\nBear this in mind when enjoying this game,\nEntrance yourself in the atmosphere of a small town, its antique shop, and the stories of the shopkeeper.\nUse your imagination.\nTry out different things not to WIN the game, but try to understand the characters, feel them and so on.\nThe atmosphere is a bit like Twin Peaks or an episode of Columbo.\nA gem game.", "hours": 1.1, "user_id": "76561198150609627", "username": "patkelus", "products": 24, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "342450", "page": 2, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2019-07-18", "text": "Sword Daughter is a 30 min short chose your own adventure/visual novel game with a female protagonist. The game is characterized by wonderful artwork, pleasant music and very well elaborated backgrounds. The inspiration is definitely in the templates from the 80-90' and is therefore a classic gamebook. If you want to experience a short adventure in between, Sword Daughter is a good choice. Personally I liked this indie game.", "hours": 0.5, "username": "Player1", "products": 539, "early_access": false}
