{"product_id": "314020", "page": 5, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2020-09-20", "text": "Summary: I loved it! I would play it again. The music, was super relaxing got me to wind down after a stressful day. The atmosphere of the bugs, grass, and little things you collect look very beautifully hand drawn. The animations are wonderful. The puzzles are easy to mid level puzzles that add a bit of difficulty but not enough to take away from the calm atmosphere for me. Would have loved to have more puzzles though.\nNote: This game has a very small hit box for items or hit boxes are not where they are supposed to be cause of the size of the monitor size (21:9). It makes clicking items frustrating.\nMusic: Very nice. I could listen to it all day.\nControls: Simple point and click or drag nothing complicated.\nArt: It all looks hand drawn with love. I loved the art for each of the five areas.\nIssues I had: The hit boxes for items in the game should be widened. With the 21:9 monitor i have the hit boxes are not in the right spot and it subtracted from the calm atmosphere of this beautiful short game.", "hours": 4.6, "user_id": "76561198337721399", "username": "LifeSongH", "products": 527, "early_access": false}
