{"product_id": "281580", "page": 3, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-31", "text": "This game is kind of like that roughed up puppy you see at the pound: you know it has fleas, its missing one eye, and damn if it isnt ugly... but it just needs a good home.\nSo here's the deal. The game is older. It runs like ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•. You'll hae to patch it yourself, and after that you'll most likely have to run through the other fixes you find on the discussion boards, and probably have to cut the draw distance to the lowest setting. Why deal with all that?\nBecause its fun. Don't get me wrong- it isnt DCS or BMS or anything like that, but for 2 dollars and change its plenty satisfying to to swoop low over a T-55 and brrrrrrrt it to death. I recomend it, but only if\n1. You aren't super serious into sims\n2. You're playing on a machine that isn't going to let the better ones run smoothly.", "hours": 12.4, "username": "theworldmoveson", "products": 375, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "281580", "page": 3, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-24", "text": "EDIT: After 2 days of trying to find some kind of fix for this game and Windows 10 I finally found one thanks to Federico Dossena (adolfintel)\n. As bizare as it as it might sound the fix is to copy 2 files from a Skyrim ENB mod\ninto the games installation folder and that fixes the fps issue in windows 10. However the game still has a couple of issues, after each mission you may get a black screen; this is easy to work around, simply alt+tab to desktop then alt+tab back to the game. The other is occasional crash to desktop after a mission.\nIf you don't mind updating and modding the game yourself; and can put up with the odd crash to desktop then Wings over Europe is a pretty good semisim game, with well modelled aircraft.\nHere's my video on how I got it working on Windows 10 x64.\n2.4 FPS! (yes two point four frames per second) on Windows 10 x64. 0% GPU usage (RX 480 8Gb). 12% CPU usage (FX8120 @4.5GHz).\nI tried many different graphics settings, downloading the patch (because Steam doesn't automatically do it) and running it in compatibility mode for Vista and XP but nothing improved the FPS to a leval that made the game playable.\nIts a shame really because the game looks pretty decent if your looking for a semi sim 3rd/4th gen fighter air combat game.", "hours": 1.4, "username": "Voodoo_S3", "products": 332, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "344340", "page": 5, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-05", "text": "was enjoying thr game until an error popped up dont wanna un install and try to reinstal yet. cant find my liscence and have heard back from support.  I'm still using the card I used to pay for the game.\nhavent figured out how to edit the rosters or draft. idk what product/progam to use to edit them and even at 100 the scouting doesnt seem on. had teams that were good current and future and lost to teams i shouldnt of too many times", "hours": 231.4, "user_id": "76561198221214924", "username": "yaunti", "products": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "344340", "page": 5, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-04-20", "text": "This game is frustrating as hell.  As much as I try to like it (as I love the stats that it generates), here are the problems.\nThe interface is from the 90's.  Horrible modal windows that need to be constantly opened and closed to the point of exhaustion.\nToo many injuries to the point of being unrealistic.  I've had several seasons completely ruined by having my roster decimated with injuries.  I dread checking the injuries after every game.  I've never seen teams completely wiped out by injuries to that extent in the NFL (to the point where I need to acquire 1 to 2 players each week just to field a freak'n team).  I shouldn't have to tweak the config settings to make injuries realistic.\nOne of my best players was \"severely depressed\" for an entire season and would not play.  I could have cut him if I wanted to pay about a $1 mil. settlement.  I know that kind of stuff happens from time to time for real, but combine that with my six players that are out for 10 weeks with broken arms, feet, clavicles etc. and it gets a little unnerving.\nThere is not enough background on players in the draft other than combine scores.  What this means is that the draft is usually a complete crap shoot.  Acquiring new staff members with good scouting ability doesn't seem to change a thing.\nI need to draft coaches...give me a break.\nI'm required to have a fullback on the roster...give me a break.  Waste of a roster spot.\nThis just names a few of the problems.", "hours": 153.8, "user_id": "76561197972369732", "username": "tanelorn", "products": 228, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "344340", "page": 5, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-26", "text": "I love this game but I would find it more entertaining if it had 3D graphical element much like OOTP 17 or Football Manager have. This series is lagging behind in that aspect and I think it would be alot more fun if we could actually see the action instead of just reading it in text.\nIt also would be fun to be able to create our own custom leagues, uniforms, and players.\nI also like to see weather and team location have greater affect on the outcome of games. Say I create a team in Anchorage Alaska. I would want the weather to be a contributing factor in the outcome of games and the statistics of the players.\nAnyway these are just some thoughts on how to improve a good game. Overall I recomend this to anyone likes Professional Football from a management aspect.", "hours": 121.6, "user_id": "76561198050395472", "username": "MoonChild", "products": 536, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "344340", "page": 5, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-25", "text": "This game is for men...who actually understand football and management...and that want their lives taken away forever. My girlfriend hates you FOF7. The end", "hours": 1679.4, "username": "Lord Malric", "products": 843, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "344340", "page": 5, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-23", "text": "If you like American football and are a stats person like myself, then this game is for you. It is, in essence, \"spreadsheet\" football in that you manage and review your rosters, gameplans and play calling through very careful analysis. There is no action to be found here.  You can either simulate your games or call your own plays that are played out via a text box.\nI'm not really a text-based fan, but my love of stats and franchise building over-rides my disdain for text based gaming. That really says something for how deep this game is. There are mountains of ever changing data that requires your analysis. Seeing the evolution of the league you create is both amazing and rewarding. Remember that 1st round defensive end you passed on because you needed a \"can't miss\" franchise quarterback? Well, seven seasons later, that DE has earned 4 bowl rings, and countless accolades while terrorizing the league. All while your 1st round bust (had a minor red flag you ignored) has battled off-field problems (illegal firearms possesion, tobacco addiction- yes, while somewhat rare, this can happen) and has been traded three times in seven years.\nYou won the superbowl? Great! But now your franchise running back wants a raise...and so does your all-league defensive player of the year. Can't afford it? Time to make cuts or trades. And it's not just the salary cap you have to watch when you make changes. You have positional chemistry and leadership to worry about as well. You finally find a decent veteran running back witth leadership and mentoring capabilities (helps with performance and development for the backfield group). Awesome! Downside? Your starting fullback and young, promising back-up running back hate him. YES, THIS GAME IS THAT DEEP.\nYou can automate almost everything if you wish. Hiring some decent coaches really helps in this area. However, auto-tasking and blindly simulating will greatly diminish what this game is all about. For me personally, taking on every decision in running a franchise for decades is pretty daunting. Having the flexibility to toggle AI assistance on and off gives my brain a break, and allows me to focus on areas of the game I like most. That's the beauty of the game. You can simulate seasons in minutes or review scouting material, game plan, and call every play of every game.\nPros:\n+ statistics galore. Everything and anything you can think of...it is all here.\n+ create your own living, breathing league. Watch it grow and evolve for as many years as you like.\n+ AI assistance with different areas of the game. Sure, it could always use more polish, but by and large, it is excellent. I would challenge you to find a better engine.\nCons:\n- the interface. It is old. It is clunky. You can get used to it, but even when you do, there are things that you just wished were more streamlined (It would be nice if there was a search button or player comparison feature). You spend more time then needed toggling back and forth between screens then there needs to be.\n- Tutorial. There is none. You can find some of what you need at the bottom of some of the pop-up screens. But that's it. You can find some info on old message boards and threads, but it can be quite a chore to find what you need. I'm still finding out new things and I'm more than 80 hours in.\n- Minor ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•...the holes for playcalling are not your traditional even numbers on the right and odd numbers on the left. YOU CAN'T JUST JUMP INTO THIS GAME. It requires hunting down information and meticulously reading every bit of small print on every screen. There are differences in the solecismic universe. You need to be aware of what they are (another example of this is that in a 3-4 defense, your weakside linebacker is considered part of the pass rush. They won't ever be in coverage).\nAll in all, this is the deepest American Football game on the market. You can certainly get used to the interface, but I do hope the developer makes improvements to it. Would I love to see a match engine like in Football Manager or Eastside Hockey League? Absolutely. But, if that can't happen, then streamlining and updating the interface to make it easier to find information and be more aesthetically pleasing would make the next iteration a better seller.", "hours": 104.8, "user_id": "76561198029704499", "username": "tora75", "products": 242, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "344340", "page": 5, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-14", "text": "My fav game in my library.  I use to simm on Madden and Football Mogul.  Nothing against those two, but this blows them out of the water.  10/10.  Best football simm on the market.", "hours": 268.2, "user_id": "76561198277855142", "username": "GassytheThird", "products": 60, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "344340", "page": 5, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-11", "text": "I'm a long time Football Manager fan and any sports sim game in general, when i brought FOFS i was not a massive fan of the NFL so at first i found the game abit hard to get the hang of. After trying the game several times and begining to follow the NFL more closley I absolutely fell in love with this game! I reccomend it to anyone that loves sports sims particulary if you love roster building and stats as the game is text based. The games interface is a little outdated but the depth of the game more than makes up for it, It also has no bugs. The game comes with all real players, the team names are not real but can be adjusted easily in the main menu to real teams. I'm addicted!!!!!!", "hours": 103.4, "user_id": "76561198039658292", "username": "De_Elusive_Yamon", "products": 59, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "344340", "page": 5, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-29", "text": "I found this game very fun, for a guy who loves to make spreadsheets to track just about everything this was right up my alley.  I remember the first time my top rated quarterback whom I'd drafted right out of college retired...that was so depressing.", "hours": 86.1, "user_id": "76561198035789474", "username": "bigjake", "products": 256, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "344340", "page": 5, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-28", "text": "This is a text based game. That being said, i love football and THIS IS THE GAME. I have literally fist pumped or yelled out loud when i found my team needing a critical stop or in desperate need of a first down and they came through. I have actually felt heavy hearted after falling to the Bengals on the final play of the game, 9-7. The stat tracking in this game is super deep. You could get lost for an hour easy just looking at your team alone. The game play is great, and can definetly be a challenge. If you really like the NFL, and are a stats person, this game was built for you.", "hours": 792.7, "user_id": "76561198014648641", "username": "drayjones007", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "344340", "page": 5, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-11", "text": "Played this game when it was FOF 2007 and, besides updates to keep it consistent with modern NFL rules, the newer entry continues the solid play of the older form. I lose myself for hours in this game, attempting to take a down-and-out franchise from nothing-to-something as the GM. Mind you the games play out in text form and the UI has remained downright ugly for nearly a decade but the bones of this product are the best when it comes to American football sims. Definitely recommended to those that love the GM/numbers side of football - it sucks you in for multiple seasons before you realize that names like Tom Brady and Peyton Manning are long since retired. $25 is a good price for a game of this caliber, well worth the investment for any stats-based-minded gamer.", "hours": 28.4, "user_id": "76561198005986038", "username": "CommandDork", "products": 158, "early_access": false}
