{"product_id": "31920", "page": 5, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2020-10-04", "text": "The Phantom of Venice is a decent mystery game, with a variety of puzzles (varying in type and difficulty), and a so-so storyline. It's entertaining for a few hours, but it falls flat when compared to other Nancy Drew titles (like Curse of Blackmoor Manor or the Last Train to Blue Moon Canyon, to name a few).\nCompared to other Nancy Drew games, the story is very shallow (at least to me) and the characters lacked their usual backstory. Their dialogue doesn't amount to much, and the characters feel very static (you only see them in one place or so, until close to the end of the game).\nPersonally, I found the map system very messy and an unnecessary addition. There are many locations listed but you only unlock a handful, and the world feels very small. There isn't much to explore, and it seems most of the events are triggered by the storyline, and not from exploring too (like in other ND games).\nThe graphics are decent and the game itself runs smoothly, even on an older laptop which is a plus. Steam overlay never works for me with older ND games, though it could be different for someone else.\nUnlike other Nancy Drew titles, this one really isn't scary. Phantom of Venice would suit younger children, though they might need help with some of the harder puzzles. The last one took me awhile, even using a guide - it was fun nonetheless, and perfectly suitable if you want to finish a game in a night or two.\nDo I rec it as a Nancy Drew game? No - I'd say skip this one unless you buy it on sale, and even then, don't expect much. However, if you're looking for a short mystery/puzzle game to play for a day or two, this one would suit you well.", "hours": 6.6, "username": "January Wren", "products": 654, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "31920", "page": 5, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2020-10-01", "text": "The entire Nancy Drew series is so much fun - but this is probably one of my top 3 favorites.  There's just so much about this game that's fun.  I've beaten it several times, too, and keep coming back to play it.", "hours": 12.8, "username": "LadyCandace", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
