{"product_id": "230820", "page": 5, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2021-08-12", "text": "A fun point & click game filled with gorgeous artwork.\nThe story is interesting with some dark moments, definitely not as kiddy as it first seems.\nThe characters are fun and a joy to interact with, though sometimes i found myself skipping some of the more tedious dialogue. It's also a shame that some dialogue is obviously reused throughout the game, though this is few and far between.\nThe last section of the game felt not as well done as the rest of the game. It became tedious, wordy and repetitive.\nAll in all i enjoyed this game, very easy to get the hang of, delightful characters, all of which are fully voice acted and decently too. The puzzles had a good mix of easy and hard. And simple mouse controls. The artwork is stunning.\nThe only downsides were the tediousness of some dialogue and a not as good end chapter.\nBut would definitely recommend this game, well worthy of a play.", "hours": 15.0, "username": "Booples_Bex", "products": 151, "early_access": false}
