{"product_id": "230820", "page": 5, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2021-07-13", "text": "Got this on sale and it was a total steal! This game can be a little frustrating at times, but overall it's pretty awesome. Dialogue, story, and graphics are much stronger than your average HOG. I only wish there was a sequel!! Here's my breakdown of the pros and cons:\nPros:\n-Imaginative, compelling story\n-Great worldbuilding\n-Beautiful art, graphics, and soundtrack\n-Charming, magical environment with interesting characters\n-High-quality voiceovers\n-Fun and often humorous dialogue\n-Addresses socially relevant issues without making them the entire focus of the story or losing the magic of the world\n-Satisfying length/play-time\n-Pretty early in the game, you get the ability to see which areas you can click on, which is really helpful because it means you don‚Äôt have to do much pixel-hunting\n-Very few mini-games, which means most of the focus is on the story\nCons:\n-The game doesn‚Äôt tell you about collectable items until you find them--this is especially annoying when you realize that one of the items is something you can only get at the very beginning of the game. MINOR SPOILER:\n-There‚Äôs a frustrating glitch that makes a bunch of the dialogue skip so you can‚Äôt hear/see what the characters are saying. However, this seems to be resolved if you quit and restart the game\n-Some puzzles are not intuitive at all--I had to look up a guide to be able to solve several of them\n-Controls aren‚Äôt explained as fully as they could be--for example, I‚Äôm pretty sure the journal provides you minor hints if you click on it, which would have been really helpful to know from the beginning, and the F3 button activates a certain ability (so every time I tried to turn up the volume, the ability would activate and I would be really confused)\n-Dialogue can at times get repetitive and tedious, but you can click through it so it‚Äôs not too bad\n-MAJOR SPOILER:", "hours": 29.1, "user_id": "76561199103651916", "username": "ninasichele", "products": 60, "early_access": false}
