{"product_id": "27900", "page": 5, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-07-19", "text": "This game could have been decent, but there are so many things holding it back.  The overall game mechanic really isn't interesting enough to keep my interest long term.  You spend about 10% of your time figuring out how to solve an area, and then 90% of your time battling the physics engine to get everything in place.  On top of that they put enemies in the game.  These are giant balls that follow you around and bump you.  So while you are battling the physics engine, you are simultaneously playing bumping cars with floating balls.  Also, there's falling damage, and if for some reason your timing is off on one of your gloves, you very likely will die.  Be prepared for lots of quick saves and quick loads.  The quick loads aren't exactly \"quick\" either.  With a non SSD expect to spend a lot of time looking at a portrait of the female protragonist while you wait to do some more trial and error.", "hours": 9.9, "username": "fightoffyourdemons", "products": 323, "early_access": false}
