{"product_id": "220700", "page": 5, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2021-10-17", "text": "^ it's OK I guess.\nNo but really jokes about my high app run time aside, this and all other RPG Maker editors are fantastic tools. They are without a doubt the easiest engine to make an RPG in, to the point that anyone can make an RPG with them... so there are admittedly some sub-par games out there which have given RPG Maker a poor reputation to some. But the massive quantity of games made in RPG Maker games do not speak for the quality of the engine negatively, they show how incredible the engine is at doing it's job of being easy enough that anyone can use it, and flexible and fully editable enough that any game can be made.\nThe *major* drawback of using RPG Maker that all new game devs should be aware of is that it is difficult to port games to non-PC platforms, especially for VX Ace, which requires doing something ridiculous like making a custom game interpreter and wrapping your game inside of it (there is *no* support for other platforms, and no one using VX Ace should *expect* to be able to publish their game on other platforms even though it is theoretically possible and you may see that such an environment does currently exist if you do some searching online). Support for other platforms by other RPG Maker versions is barely better than none, with MV pulling ahead of MZ in that department.\nSo while I would even say that VX Ace is arguably a better tool than MV or MZ, and that any RPG Maker editor is by far and away the easiest way to make an RPG if your game so much as vaguely resembles any previous RPG out there or you just want to make a game with an intuitive database GUI tool already created for you--be cautious before spending your time learning this engine, and reflect on what your end goals for your project and personal growth as a developer are, and how important supporting different platforms is to you.", "hours": 4916.2, "user_id": "76561198052357780", "username": "zadck1", "products": 73, "early_access": false}
