{"product_id": "324610", "page": 3, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-04-20", "text": "The Shopkeeper is a short, confusing, repetitive, obliquous game with a pretty bad voice acting with no subtitles to make the comprehension easier.\nThe game presents us with a young businessman looking for an antique to gift and impress his Mother-in-Law. The titular Shopkeeper tells the story behind each item for sale in his store and through a series of dialogue choices, it will be explained the consequences of choosing one gift over the other. Pick the incorrect gift and the story will repeat itself, until you pick the right one and the game ends.\nThe problem is that the story is never particularly explicit. Even when the best ending is achieved, you can‚Äôt really be sure what happened or why that approach was more successful than your previous ones. This results in each subsequent play through feel too repetitive and it becomes frustrating... very frustrating.", "hours": 2.5, "username": "Lyonesse", "products": 324, "early_access": false}
