{"product_id": "342450", "page": 3, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2019-07-17", "text": "For those who want an INEXPENSIVE & SHORT non-linear visual novel with storylines that branch out to numerous endings and easy to get all achievements, \"Sword Daughter\" is a visual novel worth checking out.\nThe visual novel is no doubt is a man's storyline and I say this because the main protagonist is a female warrior trained by her father to be a fighter.\nInstead of living up to how her father has raised her, the branching storylines paints a damsel in distress.  When you want the female character to kick some arse, instead you get a crappy ending.\nSo, for the most part, she becomes a warrior who succumbs to the alluring charm of the half human/half elf and not long into their journey, they already want to kiss each other.  Well, at least with one ending, you get to see the sword daughter reacting when elf-man wants her to be domesticated when she agrees to go home with him.\nI also noticed a few GoT questions and I will say that you will not get the fire of Dany, you will not get the braveness of Arya, you get young Sansa and how she behaved before she learned of Crown Prince Joffrey Baratheon...Granted Elf-man is not Joffrey, more like a hornier version of LoTR Legolas.\nOverall, for a cheap price visual novel on sale that cost $1.39...worthy of trying, worthy of getting if you are hardcore into achievement perfection but it's a short non-linear visual novel that one can complete in less than 5 hours, probably less than two if you don't read it all.\nBut I'll give it a thumbs up because I didn't feel like quitting the game early and felt determined in getting all endings.", "hours": 4.5, "username": "„Ç±„Éç„Éá„Ç£ (KNDY)", "products": 1967, "early_access": false}
