{"product_id": "275080", "page": 6, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-07-26", "text": "This game is kinda awful.  I bought it when it was on sale because I wanted the trading cards/badge.  I enjoy stamp collecting as a hobby, and I thought a PostMaster badge would be cute.  I tried to play the game though and... It's like a cheap, awkward, and really boring SimCity.\nI thought the instructions/controls were a bit confusing.  Or maybe they aren't and I was just too bored to really care to figure them out.  It's not like it really matted, It didn't feel like there's really any reward for doing a good job.\nAnd maybe these faults could have been forgiven if it actually felt postal related.  As I said before, I bought this because I have an interest in stamps and postal history.  If it were just a boring game I'd probably be okay with enjoying some cute postal imagery.  Unfortunately the whole thing looks uninspired.  There's nothing really to even signify you are running a post office or package delivery.  If it weren't for the shadows of generic post box shapes, I could easily assume I was running a bus route, street cleaner, ice cream truck, etc.  The most post office imagery you'll find in this game is from the trading cards.", "hours": 0.8, "username": "[nBn] CJ", "products": 121, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "342450", "page": 3, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-12-02", "text": "Sword Daughter is a short but nicely writing story.\nIt's a story about a fiercy girl and a elf that meet each other after a event, that changes girls fate of a normal day.\nAfter that encounter, the story really begins..\nThe story is filled with very good graphics and has may choices to chose from.\nI would love for story be longer, but still it's a good one. The story it self is about 5+ hours of reading/taking other paths/choices. Love also that the game has achievements. Makes it more rewarding to try and play the game fully.\nFor the nice graphics alone, I would have this beauty in my stash of goods.\nI would recommend this story specially if you new in this genre and want to try it out.\nHas a easily gameplay for the begins and is longish enough to get a feel about the genre.\nSo if you are curious...try it out!", "hours": 7.9, "user_id": "76561198308915235", "username": "Keeper Of Games", "products": 578, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "275080", "page": 6, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-23", "text": "Curator Review:\nThis 2D Isometric Casual Indie Simulation game from Excalibur is a take on what it is like to be a Postmaster. Manage your own post office and create a monopoly on the three cities in your region before your competitor! Unfortunately, this game does not have multiplayer, but it is still a great little game for casual gamers or gamers wanting to get into the simulation genre for the first time without being overwhelmed.", "hours": 9.2, "username": "Firefinch", "products": 666, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "342450", "page": 3, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-11-23", "text": "If you can get this game on sale for less than $3, it's a decent buy. While I wish the main characters took more time to fall in love (seriously, they know each other for all of a couple of hours before they're suddenly soul-mates that can't be parted), the art is pretty, the story is decently intriguing and has a lot of forking paths, and the female MC can be decently pig-headed. Plus, you can end up being kind-of married to a dragon! Not a bad buy if you want to spend a couple of hours just enjoying so pretty art and a simple story. I certainly wouldn't buy it at full price, however!", "hours": 2.3, "user_id": "76561198054326481", "username": "tanzinaahmed1", "products": 118, "early_access": false}
