{"product_id": "342450", "page": 3, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-05-27", "text": "Sword Daughter is a fantasy adventure visual novel developed by Hanabira and published by Hanako Games. As a burgeoning warrior Tyrna, daughter of the great general Hamroth, is traveling through a vast desert with her father on the way to compete in the annual Warrior Games. As the traveling caravan they are accompanying makes camp for the night it is suddenly and unsuspectingly besieged upon by a marauding band of vicious Orcs who begin killing everyone in sight. Your beloved father quickly manages to safely hide you under a Cloak of Concealment before he himself is murdered defending the caravan during the brutal attack. Even concealed, Tyrna manages to catch a blow to the head from a wildly swinging weapon during the melee and falls to the ground still hidden yet unconscious and left for dead. A short time later and still alive, young Tyrna must learn to fend for herself in the world and make some substantial choices as she vows to track down her fathers killers and rescue the remaining but captured caravaners. Prepare to follow Tyrna on a grand adventure filled with glorious battle, powerful magic, riches beyond belief and romance as she makes meaningful choices while living the life of a swordswoman. This visual novel is a licensed recreation of an original choose-your-own-adventure fantasy book from the 1980's with all new picturesque artwork and a fantastic soundtrack.\nVisually, this novel's presentation is simply breathtaking. The outstanding artwork is of the upmost quality with superb illustrations laden with beautiful colors and shading. I'm also quite happy to report that the artstyle in this title is NOT manga-inspired, not that I don't like that particular type of illustration as I very much do but it's just nice to read a visual novel on Steam from time to time that steps away from that prevalent method of art. Aurally, this V.N. is just as superb as there are an abundance of ambient sound effects present that really immerse you quite well into the story. Also, the soundtrack itself is very impressive and blends in nicely with the narrative whether you are traversing through a barren desert, engaging combatants or witnessing a rather emotional moment in the novel. The overall user interface is simple and easy to use which allows you to focus on the reason that you are here for in the first place which is the captivating narrative. In summary, Sword Daughter puts forth a very impressive visual and aural presentation for this quite interesting visual novel experience.\nSeeing as how I couldn't get my hands on enough copies of choose-your-own adventure books to peruse, I completely loved the story in Sword Daughter and the nostalgia that it awakened in me for that particular genre of reading. There was always just something so spectacular about the choose-your-own adventure books and this visual novel managed to capture that \"special something\" perfectly. If you like to read and have never experienced this genre before then I wholeheartedly suggest that you give it a try because you won't be dissapointed. With that said, replayability is quite high as the very nature of choose-your-own adventure books warrant such a thing. As far as options go, there are numerous Steam Achievements to hunt down and Steam Trading Cards to collect as well. The title also has basic game options like sound/volume control, text speed and language selection. Also, there is a C.G. gallery that unlocks as the story progresses, an Achievement screen to keep track of your various accomplishments in the novel, a section map for determining the choices that you selected in order to help you get to the twenty two different endings and a jukebox for the wonderfully orchestrated soundtrack. In the end, this V.N. does a wonderful job of taking you on a fantastic journey packed with combat, intrigue, romance and choice which is what any worthy visual novel should be capable of doing therefore Sword Daughter is HIGHLY RECOMMENDED to any fan of the genre.", "hours": 2.7, "username": "œÅ–æ—ïŒπ—Ç—è–æ–∏_", "products": 648, "early_access": false}
