{"product_id": "27900", "page": 6, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-24", "text": "- Controls feel sluggish, as if walking through molasses. This is amplified by the footstep sounds the devs chose - big fat stompy boots. Walking backwards is like half the speed of walking forward. Mind, this character is supposed to be a trained athlete.\n- The cutscenes are terribly long-winded and drawn out. Especially during the tutorial, the computer keeps taking control away from you to tell you what is actually completely obvious in sight. Even afterwards, the computer keeps talking to you as if you were a child with special needs, and I don't mean in an AI-with-an-attitude-like manner.\n- The physics are dodgy - objects sometimes bounce around as if they weighed nothing, were made from rubber AND had no air resistance whatsoever.\n- Falling threat, the immediate experience how dangerous your current fall is, is nonexistent. There is not enough feedback (cam shake, wind noise) to give proper impression on your fall, so you die, die and die.\n- All sounds and voice-overs are completely void of reverb. At no point in the game (read: the half hour or so I managed to hold out playing this turd) does the sound of voices and noises match the room they happen in. Even a large metal corridor will make the same impression as a sound-proofed cell.\n- The glove mechanics is pointlessly slowed. There is absolutely no reason for the \"recharge time\" other than to draw this game into a tedious crawl.\n- Loading times. With the low quality of graphical assets, resetting to checkpoints should take the blink of an eye, especially from an SSD, but instead one waits for what seems like the regrowing of an eye ... absolutely abyssmal.\nAll of the flaws above could have been fixed with proper game testing which would have made a cool game even with the low-budget mocap or intro cutscene or texture quality.\nSorry, but this game sucks salty monkey balls, and you don't even get to marvel at Ashley's butt.", "hours": 0.6, "user_id": "76561198025693087", "username": "andersenman", "products": 283, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
