{"product_id": "220700", "page": 6, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2021-08-23", "text": "This is excellent software to learn the basics of game development and build your first game with. It's easy and intuitive to use for the beginner, but offers a ridiculous amount of more complex features (such as scripting to add additional functionality, and importing your own custom graphics/music) for the advanced user.\nIt's honestly a fairly robust and flexible game engine when you know how to get under the hood and really start turning gears. I was actually pretty impressed with it and spent quite a bit of time with it, even spending a few hundred additional hours learning pixel art so I could make my own graphics.\nSpend the time to learn how to properly use it and you can make some pretty cool games to share with your friends and even upload to rpgmaker game websites. There's plenty of forums, guides, youtube videos, and other resources available if you need help or even need a custom script written. I've personally found the rpgmaker community to be very welcoming and helpful whenever I had a question.", "hours": 450.5, "user_id": "76561198118709568", "username": "Valtiel", "products": 116, "early_access": false}
