{"product_id": "324610", "page": 4, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-05", "text": "Usually I don‚Äôt refund games when they are bad, only when they are broken or don‚Äôt work properly (anymore). In this case I did it even when I didn‚Äôt pay much during the winter sale.\nThe Shopkeeper has a neat premise but the execution is horrible. There is not much here but the repetition of the same sequences of three screens with the same short and uninspired lines of dialogue. The gameplay consists of nothing than clicking some random objects, listening to the same repetitive dialogues and waiting for some random achievements to pop up. There‚Äôs neither an enjoyable game nor any meaning or engaging story to witness here. It starts boring and continues being it with no hope for getting something out of the experience, as the game pretty much goes on on its own with the player only clicking randomly on the screen.\nFurthermore, the game mechanics just don‚Äôt work in the way they seem to be meant. They won‚Äôt be explained in any way and therefore you are thrown into the game without anything useful to do and trying to figure out, what there is to do. Unfortunately, there IS nothing to do, really.\nOn top of that, the dialogues are dreadfully written and the voice acting is not very good. Also there are no subtitles which would be very useful. (Note for these las sentences that I am not a native English speaker and therefore have a blurry look on this topic).\nThe art style is neat but gets wasted in the three screens that come over and over again. So the art style gets boring very fast and very undeserved.\nIt is a shame to give this game a bad review seen what it could be, that it looks relatively good and that the premises gameplay and story wise are interesting. But as bad as the execution is, it is needed.\nGet this game in case you feel lucky or very intrigued. There are people who seemed to enjoy it very much. And in case you won‚Äôt like it, you can always refund it.", "hours": 0.5, "username": "Son of a submariner", "products": 603, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "324610", "page": 4, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-01", "text": "The Shopkeeper is a short story, point and click game in which you will step into the shoes of someone who needs to buy a present for his rich mother in law, hoping to impress her and eventually receive money through a business offer.\nThe game itself is a slow paced, repetitive, and it's annoying replay system in which you have to select multiple shop items to hear their little story in which you will gather information about the outcome  of giving  that gift.\nAs this is a short story, point and click game i think it should be treated for what it is, not anything fancy, no interaction whatsoever, no subtitles, no freedom at all, you can listen to a dialogue of different items,a small dialogue selection with your mother in law, and that's all, with a beautiful short story.\nI recommend it when it's on a bundle or a good sale price, for a couple hours of casual clicking and listening to a short story i think it would be worth it.", "hours": 3.7, "username": "TEST", "products": 4507, "early_access": false}
