{"product_id": "32470", "page": 5, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2022-01-16", "text": "Short review: get this game\nMedium review: despite the ravages of time and my constant on and off not wanting to play anything this game always draws me to it no matter what mood im in definitely get this game\nLong review: as someone who has 700+ hour into this game (on steam alone) and who has owned the disc for eaw and owned the 2 discs for foc twice i have a lot of playtime and experience with this game i couldn't go without this game in my life once i heard this game was updated on steam i got it as soon as i could ill gladly spend money on infinite copies of this game while the base eaw is decent overall it has some features missing that foc includes mainly the single ship in space battle and units not constantly moving when hyperspaced in some mods make base eaw interesting to play but still those 2 features persist now for foc is much more enjoyable to me yes even with the annoying corruption of the zann consortium my only complaint is the inability to play the rebel and empire campaigns from the base game or even better new campaigns for them but despite these small issues its always been enjoyable to me now onto the mods ive made a few mods for this game (let me tell you xml editing is really easy) and have played a majority of the older and newer mods for years the best mods imo is yoden mod foc alliance awakening of the rebellion and corey loses thrawns revenge and fall of the republic mods all of these except for yoden mod make me feel like im playing a brand new game i love yoden mod because it combines empire at war with pure chaos and lots of everything this game is definitely one of the best games for me ill always rank it #1", "hours": 816.4, "username": "Catman587", "products": 192, "early_access": false}
