{"product_id": "342450", "page": 4, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-07-09", "text": "Interactive fiction has moved forward a lot since this was written in the 1980s. Despite my downvote, many users may find the camp factor of old-time  thud and blunder very entertaining. The art is also rather good, with a dragon lowering his head into shot that scared me senseless. Apart from that, however, the story and worldbuilding are shallow, its harder to get bad endings than good ones, killing the tension, and many good endings are rather monotonously similar. Someone thinking of buying this should at least think twice.", "hours": 1.4, "user_id": "76561198327901000", "username": "Ghostfriendly", "products": 151, "early_access": false}
