{"product_id": "342450", "page": 4, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-02", "text": "The story is short and relatively cohesive. If you're only going for one or two playthroughs, it's pretty solid. It's got a great art style, the sound scape is spot on, and the story telling is engaging.\nI wouldn't recommend it, though, for the reasons below:\nUnfortunately there isn't much of a 'choice' between falling in love with an elven stud and going on your own adventure. Most of the endings result in the two falling in love and herione blindly following Gavin's lead (there is only ONE time in the entire game where you have the option to be forward with him). Some endings the herione is pleased with the outcome and some she's like: uh, wait, hold up. Either way, it gets fairly boring and repetative. Can't we just be friends? Sword buddies? Teach me the elvish ways, not swoop me in your arms and drag me home to your mother.\nAlso the overarching story starts to fall apart the more you play through it. The passage of time is unclear, but the prisoners meet vastly different fates in some of the endings - but when you save them you always save the same dude. Why are the prisoners being moved around so much, why are the prisoners even there, why was the raiding party sent out in the first place? And then there are all these other questions: who is the REAL leader and decision-maker for our evil-doers, why are they even hanging out together, how did they come to set up camp there, WHY ARE THEY BUILDING THE THINGS THEY ARE BUILDING AND WHAT PURPOSE DO THEY EVEN SERVE?? Like?? I have so many more questions and playing more just made me more confused.\nOne last thing: the herione doesn't have much agency. She gets to make a few of the choices, but elf-stud talks more than she does, does all the cool stuff, and generally makes himself out to be an action hero while our herione gets herself into trouble. Like, okay, cool you can do that once or twice but eventually it just gets boring. We understand that our herione is naive and stubborn and a young warrior whose not that experienced in battle, we GET IT, but if our herione were a hero instead she'd get to do a lot more cool things.", "hours": 1.8, "user_id": "76561198048136838", "username": "FFoosiez", "products": 184, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
